title: Where Are the Veterans in the Presidential Race?
text:
Where Are the Veterans? This year's presidential field has only three candidates with military experience. By Paul D. Shinkman Oct. 15, 2015 | 12:50 p.m. EDT
+ More 'Good wars" have previously yielded good presidents, from Grant to Eisenhower. And the last decade has seen some of the most inventive leadership on foreign battlefields than any previous military. So why aren't more generals and admirals trying to lead the country that sent them to fight?
